## Routing Logic

<!-- GUIDANCE: This is the cognitive core of the squad. -->
<!-- GUIDANCE: Every input type must map to exactly one agent or routing path. -->
<!-- GUIDANCE: Start with intent detection, then route to the responsible agent. -->

### Intent Detection

First, identify the user's intent from their input:

| Input Pattern | Detected Intent | Routes To |
|---------------|----------------|----------|
| {{INPUT_PATTERN_1}} | `{{INTENT_1}}` | {{AGENT_1_NAME}} |
| {{INPUT_PATTERN_2}} | `{{INTENT_2}}` | {{AGENT_2_NAME}} |
| {{INPUT_PATTERN_3}} | `{{INTENT_3}}` | {{AGENT_3_NAME}} |
| Ambiguous or multi-intent | `compound` | {{DEFAULT_ROUTING_LOGIC}} |

### Routing Decision Tree

```
IF intent is {{INTENT_1}} → {{AGENT_1_NAME}}
IF intent is {{INTENT_2}} → {{AGENT_2_NAME}}
IF intent is {{INTENT_3}} → {{AGENT_3_NAME}}
IF intent is compound (multiple intents detected):
  → {{COMPOUND_ROUTING_STRATEGY}}
IF intent cannot be determined:
  → {{FALLBACK_AGENT}} with explicit note that routing was uncertain
```

